title: Bitter loss for ESU against Ship after 5 overtimes
text: Bitter loss for ESU against Ship after 5 overtimes Comment Posted Oct. 3, 2015 at 10:55 PM Posted Oct. 3, 2015 at 10:55 PM Â» Social News After leading 41-14 with 5:03 left in the game, East Stroudburg University fell 69-67 (5 OT) to Shippensburg on Saturday night. Quarterback Matt Soltes finished the night 40-for-70 with 594 passing yards and nine touchdowns. Wide receiver Jon Schnaars, pictured (5), caught 20 passes for 218 yards and seven touchdowns. Wide receiever Gerard Wendowski caught 10 passes for 222 yards and two touchdowns. poconorecord.com
